Comment: I had to annotate this game. I had a winning position, a superior passed pawn and I was very lucky to get a draw. I made a couple of seriously poor decisions around move 28.

Was not sure the reason for the Bishop retreat. It opens up my black diagonal perfectly when I do the natural reply of f5. Black's white bishop becomes somewhat useless. It gives me the initiative and black is somewhat cramped.
